.TH "HTMLInputElement.select_event" "JS" "July 7, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLInputElement.select_event \- HTMLInputElement: select event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]select\f[B]\f[R] event fires when some text has been
selected.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\[dq]select\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {});

onselect = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {};
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Selection logger
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]input\f[R] value=\[dq]Try selecting some text in this element.\[dq] />
<\f[B]p\f[R] id=\[dq]log\[dq]></\f[B]p\f[R]>
.EE
.IP
.EX
\f[B]function\f[R] logSelection(event) {
  \f[B]const\f[R] log = document.getElementById(\[dq]log\[dq]);
  \f[B]const\f[R] selection = event.target.value.substring(
    event.target.selectionStart,
    event.target.selectionEnd,
  );
  log.textContent = \[ga]You selected: ${selection}\[ga];
}

\f[B]const\f[R] input = document.querySelector(\[dq]input\[dq]);
input.addEventListener(\[dq]select\[dq], logSelection);
.EE
.SS onselect equivalent
You can also set up the event handler using the \f[CR]onselect\f[R]
property:
.IP
.EX
input.onselect = logSelection;
.EE
